hopobject.body: Do you play any instruments? pos t vac manual The company is calling the Lumia 625 'hero of the big screen' presumable because the phone packs a large display. What's more, Nokia claims the panel is viewable in direct sunlight and is super-sensitive, allowing for operation with gloves hands or even nails. The display itself measures 4.7 inches in size and is a WVGA panel with 201 ppi. Display aside, the phone runs on a 1.2 GHz dual-core Snapdragon S4, 512 MB of RAM, 8 GB of storage (up to 64 GB via SD card), a 5-megapixel camera, and support for USB 2.0, Bluetooth 4.0, and WLAN IEEE 802.11b/g/n.
